11 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Department of
Agriculture, Food, and Forestry; requiring the
12 Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and
Forestry to reimburse agricultural operations for
13 losses in certain circumstances; providing for
codification; and providing an effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 4030 of Title 2, unless there is
19 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 The Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry shall
21 be liable and shall fully reimburse agricultural operations for
22 economic losses resulting from actions taken by the agency in
23 enforcing and implementing a court order from a suit in which the
24 prevailing plaintiff was the Oklahoma Attorney General.
Req. No. 17254 Page 1

1 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
